  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Interactive Decision Tree Explorer</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    margin: 1em;\n  }\n  input[type=text], input[type=number] {\n    width: 10em;\n  }\n  textarea {\n    width: 100%;\n    height: 6em;\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n  }\n  button {\n    margin: 0.2em 0.4em 0.2em 0;\n  }\n  label {\n    display: inline-block;\n    width: 14em;\n  }\n  #node-list {\n    max-height: 12em;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 0.4em;\n  }\n  #message {\n    font-weight: bold;\n    margin: 1em 0 0.5em 0;\n  }\n  #tree-output {\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    margin-top: 1em;\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 0.4em;\n    max-height: 18em;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n    font-size: 0.9em;\n  }\n  #path-trace {\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    margin-top: 1em;\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 0.4em;\n    max-height: 12em;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n    font-size: 0.9em;\n  }\n  hr {\n    margin:1em 0;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Decision Tree Explorer</h1>\n\n<p>\nThis tool lets you build, edit, and explore decision trees interactively. You can create nodes representing questions or decisions, connect nodes via branches with conditions, and simulate decision flow. \n</p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<section>\n<h2>1. Create / Edit Nodes</h2>\n<p>Nodes represent points in your decision tree. Each node has a label (question or decision) and can have multiple branches connecting to other nodes.</p>\n\n<label for=\"new-node-label\">New Node Label:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"new-node-label\" placeholder=\"e.g. Is it raining?\" />\n<button id=\"btn-add-node\">Add Node</button>\n<button id=\"btn-clear-all\">Clear All Nodes & Paths</button>\n\n<div id=\"message\" aria-live=\"polite\"></div>\n\n<h3>Existing Nodes:</h3>\n<div id=\"node-list\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-label=\"List of nodes\">\n  <!-- Dynamic list -->\n</div>\n\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<section>\n<h2>2. Add / Manage Branches (Edges)</h2>\n<p>Define edges (branches) from one node to another with a condition label.</p>\n\n<form id=\"branch-form\">\n  <label for=\"branch-from\">From Node:</label>\n  <select id=\"branch-from\" required></select>\n\n  <label for=\"branch-condition\">Condition Label:</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"branch-condition\" placeholder=\"e.g. Yes\" required />\n\n  <label for=\"branch-to\">To Node:</label>\n  <select id=\"branch-to\" required></select>\n\n  <button type=\"submit\">Add Branch</button>\n</form>\n\n<p><small>Note: Branch conditions help guide decisions from one node to another.</small></p>\n\n<button id=\"btn-clear-branches\">Clear All Branches</button>\n<div id=\"branches-list\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-label=\"List of branches\" style=\"max-height:9em;overflow-y:auto;border:1px solid black;padding:0.4em;margin-top:0.5em;\"></div>\n\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<section>\n<h2>3. Simulation Mode</h2>\n<p>Explore the decision tree by simulating choices from a start node. You can select a start node and navigate through decisions.</p>\n\n<label for=\"sim-start-node\">Select Start Node:</label>\n<select id=\"sim-start-node\"></select>\n<button id=\"btn-start-sim\">Start Simulation</button>\n\n<div id=\"sim-container\" style=\"margin-top:1em;\"></div>\n<button id=\"btn-end-sim\" style=\"display:none;margin-top:0.8em;\">End Simulation</button>\n\n<div id=\"path-trace\" aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"display:none;\" aria-label=\"Simulation path trace\"></div>\n\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<section>\n<h2>4. Import / Export Decision Tree (JSON)</h2>\n\n<label for=\"json-textarea\">Paste JSON Below:</label>\n<textarea id=\"json-textarea\" aria-label=\"Decision tree JSON\"></textarea>\n<br />\n<button id=\"btn-import-json\">Import JSON</button>\n<button id=\"btn-export-json\">Export Current Tree as JSON</button>\n\n<div id=\"json-message\" aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"margin-top:0.5em;\"></div>\n\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<section>\n<h2>5. Analysis & Exploration Tools</h2>\n\n<button id=\"btn-validate-tree\">Validate Tree (Check for unconnected nodes, cycles)</button>\n<button id=\"btn-show-depth\">Show Tree Depth</button>\n<button id=\"btn-show-leaves\">Show Leaf Nodes</button>\n\n<div id=\"analysis-output\" aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"margin-top:1em;white-space: pre-wrap; max-height: 20em; overflow-y: auto; border: 1px solid black; padding: 0.4em; font-size: 0.9em;\"></div>\n\n</section>\n\n<script>\n(function(){\n  \"use strict\";\n\n  // Data structure: \n  // nodes = Map of nodeId -> {label:string, branches: [ { condition:string, toNodeId:string } ] }\n  // nodeId is numeric string, incremental\n\n  let nodes = new Map();\n  let nextNodeId = 1;\n\n  // Sim state\n  let simActive = false;\n  let simCurrentNodeId = null;\n  let simPath = []; // array of { nodeId, choiceCondition }\n\n  // HTML elements references\n  const inputNewNodeLabel = document.getElementById('new-node-label');\n  const btnAddNode = document.getElementById('btn-add-node');\n  const btnClearAll = document.getElementById('btn-clear-all');\n  const nodeListDiv = document.getElementById('node-list');\n  const messageDiv = document.getElementById('message');\n\n  const branchForm = document.getElementById('branch-form');\n  const branchFromSelect = document.getElementById('branch-from');\n  const branchToSelect = document.getElementById('branch-to');\n  const branchConditionInput = document.getElementById('branch-condition');\n  const branchesListDiv = document.getElementById('branches-list');\n  const btnClearBranches = document.getElementById('btn-clear-branches');\n\n  const simStartNodeSelect = document.getElementById('sim-start-node');\n  const btnStartSim = document.getElementById('btn-start-sim');\n  const simContainerDiv = document.getElementById('sim-container');\n  const btnEndSim = document.getElementById('btn-end-sim');\n  const pathTraceDiv = document.getElementById('path-trace');\n\n  const jsonTextarea = document.getElementById('json-textarea');\n  const btnImportJson = document.getElementById('btn-import-json');\n  const btnExportJson = document.getElementById('btn-export-json');\n  const jsonMessageDiv = document.getElementById('json-message');\n\n  const btnValidateTree = document.getElementById('btn-validate-tree');\n  const btnShowDepth = document.getElementById('btn-show-depth');\n  const btnShowLeaves = document.getElementById('btn-show-leaves');\n  const analysisOutputDiv = document.getElementById('analysis-output');\n\n  // Utilities\n\n  function resetMessage() {\n    messageDiv.textContent = '';\n    jsonMessageDiv.textContent = '';\n    analysisOutputDiv.textContent = '';\n  }\n\n  function displayMessage(msg, isError = false) {\n    messageDiv.textContent = msg;\n    messageDiv.style.color = isError ? 'red' : 'black';\n  }\n  function displayJsonMessage(msg, isError = false) {\n    jsonMessageDiv.textContent = msg;\n    jsonMessageDiv.style.color = isError ? 'red' : 'black';\n  }\n  function displayAnalysis(msg) {\n    analysisOutputDiv.textContent = msg;\n  }\n\n  function sanitizeLabel(label) {\n    return label.trim().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n  }\n\n  // Node management\n\n  function addNode(label) {\n    if (!label) return null;\n    let nodeId = String(nextNodeId++);\n    nodes.set(nodeId, { label: label, branches: [] });\n    return nodeId;\n  }\n\n  function deleteNode(nodeId) {\n    if (!nodes.has(nodeId)) return false;\n\n    // Remove the node\n    nodes.delete(nodeId);\n\n    // Remove any branches referencing this node\n    for (let [nid, node] of nodes.entries()) {\n      node.branches = node.branches.filter(branch => branch.toNodeId !== nodeId);\n    }\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Branch management\n\n  function addBranch(fromNodeId, condition, toNodeId) {\n    if (!nodes.has(fromNodeId)) return false;\n    if (!nodes.has(toNodeId)) return false;\n    if (!condition) return false;\n\n    let node = nodes.get(fromNodeId);\n    // Do not allow duplicate condition on same node\n    let exists = node.branches.some(b => b.condition === condition);\n    if (exists) return false;\n\n    node.branches.push({ condition: condition, toNodeId: toNodeId });\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  function deleteBranch(fromNodeId, condition) {\n    if (!nodes.has(fromNodeId)) return false;\n    let node = nodes.get(fromNodeId);\n    let before = node.branches.length;\n    node.branches = node.branches.filter(b => b.condition !== condition);\n    return before !== node.branches.length;\n  }\n\n  function clearAllBranches() {\n    for (let node of nodes.values()) {\n      node.branches = [];\n    }\n  }\n\n  // UI refresh functions\n\n  function refreshNodeList() {\n    nodeListDiv.innerHTML = '';\n    if (nodes.size === 0) {\n      nodeListDiv.textContent = '(No nodes created yet)';\n      return;\n    }\n    for (let [id, node] of nodes.entries()) {\n      let div = document.createElement('div');\n      div.tabIndex = -1;\n      let branchesStr = node.branches.length > 0\n        ? node.branches.map(b => `[${b.condition}]→${nodes.get(b.toNodeId)?.label ?? '(broken)'} (id:${b.toNodeId})`).join('; ')\n        : '(no branches)';\n      div.textContent = `ID:${id} - ${node.label} → ${branchesStr}`;\n\n      // Add delete node button for each node\n      let delBtn = document.createElement('button');\n      delBtn.textContent = 'Delete Node';\n      delBtn.style.marginLeft = '0.8em';\n      delBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n        if(simActive) {\n          alert('Stop simulation before deleting nodes.');\n          return;\n        }\n        if(confirm(`Delete node ID:${id} \"${node.label}\" and all referencing branches?`)) {\n          deleteNode(id);\n          refreshAll();\n          resetSimulation();\n          displayMessage(`Deleted node ID:${id}`, false);\n        }\n      });\n      div.appendChild(delBtn);\n\n      nodeListDiv.appendChild(div);\n    }\n  }\n\n  function refreshBranchDropdowns() {\n    // for branch-from and branch-to selects\n    let fragFrom = document.createDocumentFragment();\n    let fragTo = document.createDocumentFragment();\n\n    if (nodes.size === 0) {\n      branchFromSelect.innerHTML = \"\";\n      branchToSelect.innerHTML = \"\";\n      return;\n    }\n    // Sort nodes by id numeric ascending\n    let sortedNodes = Array.from(nodes.entries()).sort(([a], [b]) => (+a) - (+b));\n    sortedNodes.forEach(([id, node]) => {\n      let optFrom = document.createElement('option');\n      optFrom.value = id;\n      optFrom.textContent = `ID:${id} - ${node.label}`;\n      fragFrom.appendChild(optFrom);\n\n      let optTo = document.createElement('option');\n      optTo.value = id;\n      optTo.textContent = `ID:${id} - ${node.label}`;\n      fragTo.appendChild(optTo);\n    });\n    branchFromSelect.innerHTML = '';\n    branchToSelect.innerHTML = '';\n    branchFromSelect.appendChild(fragFrom);\n    branchToSelect.appendChild(fragTo);\n\n    // Also refresh sim start node select\n    refreshSimStartNodeSelect();\n  }\n\n  function refreshBranchesList() {\n    branchesListDiv.innerHTML = '';\n    let totalBranches = 0;\n    for(let [id, node] of nodes.entries()) {\n      if(node.branches.length === 0) continue;\n      node.branches.forEach(branch => {\n        let bdiv = document.createElement('div');\n        bdiv.tabIndex = -1;\n        let toLabel = nodes.get(branch.toNodeId)?.label ?? '(broken)';\n        bdiv.textContent = `From ID:${id} (${node.label}) [${branch.condition}] → ID:${branch.toNodeId} (${toLabel})`;\n\n        // Add delete branch button\n        let delBbtn = document.createElement('button');\n        delBbtn.textContent = 'Delete Branch';\n        delBbtn.style.marginLeft = '0.8em';\n        delBbtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n          if(simActive) {\n            alert('Stop simulation before deleting branches.');\n            return;\n          }\n          if(confirm(`Delete this branch (From ID:${id} condition [${branch.condition}])?`)) {\n            deleteBranch(id, branch.condition);\n            refreshAll();\n            resetSimulation();\n            displayMessage('Branch deleted.', false);\n          }\n        });\n        bdiv.appendChild(delBbtn);\n\n        branchesListDiv.appendChild(bdiv);\n        totalBranches++;\n      });\n    }\n    if(totalBranches === 0){\n      branchesListDiv.textContent = '(No branches defined)';\n    }\n  }\n\n  function refreshSimStartNodeSelect() {\n    let prevVal = simStartNodeSelect.value;\n    simStartNodeSelect.innerHTML = '';\n    if(nodes.size === 0) {\n      let opt = document.createElement('option');\n      opt.textContent = '(no nodes)';\n      opt.value = '';\n      simStartNodeSelect.appendChild(opt);\n      return;\n    }\n    let sorted = Array.from(nodes.entries()).sort(([a], [b]) => (+a) - (+b));\n    for(let [id, node] of sorted){\n      let opt = document.createElement('option');\n      opt.value = id;\n      opt.textContent = `ID:${id} - ${node.label}`;\n      simStartNodeSelect.appendChild(opt);\n    }\n    if(prevVal && nodes.has(prevVal)) {\n      simStartNodeSelect.value = prevVal;\n    }\n  }\n\n  function refreshAll() {\n    resetMessage();\n    refreshNodeList();\n    refreshBranchDropdowns();\n    refreshBranchesList();\n  }\n\n  // Simulation functions\n\n  function resetSimulation() {\n    simActive = false;\n    simCurrentNodeId = null;\n    simPath = [];\n    simContainerDiv.innerHTML = '';\n    btnEndSim.style.display = 'none';\n    pathTraceDiv.style.display = 'none';\n    pathTraceDiv.textContent = '';\n    btnStartSim.disabled = false;\n    simStartNodeSelect.disabled = false;\n  }\n\n  function startSimulation(startNodeId) {\n    if (!nodes.has(startNodeId)) {\n      alert('Start node does not exist.');\n      return;\n    }\n    simActive = true;\n    simCurrentNodeId = startNodeId;\n    simPath = [{nodeId: startNodeId, choiceCondition: null}]; // first node, no choice yet\n\n    btnStartSim.disabled = true;\n    simStartNodeSelect.disabled = true;\n    btnEndSim.style.display = 'inline';\n    pathTraceDiv.style.display = 'block';\n    updateSimulationUI();\n  }\n\n  function endSimulation() {\n    resetSimulation();\n    displayMessage('Simulation ended.', false);\n  }\n\n  function updateSimulationUI() {\n    simContainerDiv.innerHTML = '';\n\n    if(!simActive || !simCurrentNodeId) return;\n\n    let currentNode = nodes.get(simCurrentNodeId);\n    if(!currentNode) {\n      simContainerDiv.textContent = 'Current node not found.';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Show current node label:\n    let pNodeLabel = document.createElement('p');\n    pNodeLabel.textContent = `Current Node [ID:${simCurrentNodeId}]: ${currentNode.label}`;\n    simContainerDiv.appendChild(pNodeLabel);\n\n    if(currentNode.branches.length === 0){\n      // Leaf node - no branches:\n      let pLeaf = document.createElement('p');\n      pLeaf.textContent = \"(Leaf node - no further branches)\";\n      simContainerDiv.appendChild(pLeaf);\n      updatePathTrace();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Show choices as buttons:\n    let choicesContainer = document.createElement('div');\n    choicesContainer.setAttribute('role', 'list');\n    choicesContainer.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Decision choices from current node');\n    for(let branch of currentNode.branches){\n      let btnChoice = document.createElement('button');\n      let toLabel = nodes.get(branch.toNodeId)?.label ?? '(broken)';\n      btnChoice.textContent = `[${branch.condition}] → ${toLabel}`;\n      btnChoice.setAttribute('role', 'listitem');\n      btnChoice.addEventListener('click', () => {\n        chooseBranch(branch.condition, branch.toNodeId);\n      });\n      choicesContainer.appendChild(btnChoice);\n    }\n    simContainerDiv.appendChild(choicesContainer);\n\n    updatePathTrace();\n  }\n\n  function chooseBranch(condition, toNodeId) {\n    if (!nodes.has(toNodeId)) {\n      alert('Target node does not exist.');\n      return;\n    }\n    simCurrentNodeId = toNodeId;\n    simPath.push({nodeId: toNodeId, choiceCondition: condition});\n    updateSimulationUI();\n  }\n\n  function updatePathTrace() {\n    let lines = [];\n    lines.push('Decision Path Trace:');\n    for(let i=0; i<simPath.length; i++){\n      let step = simPath[i];\n      let node = nodes.get(step.nodeId);\n      let line = `${i+1}. Node [ID:${step.nodeId}]: ${node?.label ?? '(broken)'}`\n      if(i > 0){\n        line += `  (via condition [${step.choiceCondition}])`;\n      }\n      lines.push(line);\n    }\n    pathTraceDiv.textContent = lines.join('\\n');\n  }\n\n  // Import/Export functions\n\n  function exportToJson() {\n    // export nodes as array of objects with id, label, branches.\n    let arr = Array.from(nodes.entries()).map(([id, node]) => {\n      return { id, label: node.label, branches: node.branches.slice() };\n    });\n    return JSON.stringify(arr, null, 2);\n  }\n\n  function importFromJson(text) {\n    try {\n      let arr = JSON.parse(text);\n      if(!Array.isArray(arr)) throw new Error('Invalid format: Expected an array.');\n      let tempNodes = new Map();\n      let maxId = 0;\n\n      for(let obj of arr){\n        if(typeof obj.id !== 'string' && typeof obj.id !== 'number'){\n          throw new Error('Node id must be string or number.');\n        }\n        let id = String(obj.id);\n        if(tempNodes.has(id)){\n          throw new Error(`Duplicate node id found: ${id}`);\n        }\n        if(typeof obj.label !== 'string'){\n          throw new Error('Node label must be string.');\n        }\n        if(!Array.isArray(obj.branches)){\n          throw new Error('Node branches must be array.');\n        }\n        // Validate branches\n        for(let b of obj.branches){\n          if(typeof b.condition !== 'string') throw new Error('Branch condition must be string.');\n          if(typeof b.toNodeId !== 'string' && typeof b.toNodeId !== 'number') throw new Error('Branch toNodeId must be string or number.');\n        }\n        tempNodes.set(id, {label: obj.label, branches: obj.branches.map(b => ({condition: b.condition, toNodeId: String(b.toNodeId)}))});\n        let numericId = (+id);\n        if(!isNaN(numericId) && numericId > maxId){\n          maxId = numericId;\n        }\n      }\n      // Verify all branch targets exist\n      for(let [nid, node] of tempNodes.entries()){\n        for(let branch of node.branches){\n          if(!tempNodes.has(branch.toNodeId)){\n            throw new Error(`Branch target node ID:${branch.toNodeId} not found for branch from node ID:${nid}`);\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      // All good - replace current nodes\n      nodes = tempNodes;\n      nextNodeId = maxId + 1;\n      resetSimulation();\n      refreshAll();\n      displayJsonMessage('Import successful.', false);\n      return true;\n    }catch(e){\n      displayJsonMessage('Import error: ' + e.message, true);\n      return false;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Analysis and Exploration\n\n  // Detect unconnected nodes\n  function findUnconnectedNodes() {\n    if(nodes.size === 0) return [];\n\n    // Consider a node connected if it is reachable from any root node (node without inbound edges)\n    // First find inbound edges count:\n    let inbound = new Map();\n    for(let nodeId of nodes.keys()){\n      inbound.set(nodeId, 0);\n    }\n    for(let node of nodes.values()){\n      for(let b of node.branches){\n        if(inbound.has(b.toNodeId)) inbound.set(b.toNodeId, inbound.get(b.toNodeId)+1);\n      }\n    }\n    // roots = nodes with zero inbound edges\n    let roots = Array.from(inbound.entries()).filter(([nid, count]) => count === 0).map(([nid]) => nid);\n    if(roots.length === 0){\n      // Then all nodes have inbound edges, treat all nodes as roots to check connectivity:\n      roots = Array.from(nodes.keys());\n    }\n\n    let visited = new Set();\n\n    function dfs(nid) {\n      if(visited.has(nid)) return;\n      visited.add(nid);\n      let node = nodes.get(nid);\n      if(!node) return;\n      node.branches.forEach(b => dfs(b.toNodeId));\n    }\n    roots.forEach(rid => dfs(rid));\n\n    let unconnected = [];\n    for(let nid of nodes.keys()){\n      if(!visited.has(nid)){\n        unconnected.push(nid);\n      }\n    }\n    return unconnected;\n  }\n\n  // Detect cycles using DFS White/Grey/Black coloring\n  function findCycles() {\n    let color = new Map(); // white=0, grey=1, black=2\n    for(let nid of nodes.keys()){\n      color.set(nid, 0);\n    }\n    let cycles = [];\n    let stack = [];\n\n    function dfs(nodeId) {\n      color.set(nodeId, 1);\n      stack.push(nodeId);\n      let node = nodes.get(nodeId);\n      for(let b of node.branches){\n        let toId = b.toNodeId;\n        let c = color.get(toId);\n        if(c === 0){\n          if(dfs(toId)) return true;\n        } else if(c === 1){\n          // cycle found - get cycle path from stack\n          let idx = stack.indexOf(toId);\n          let cyclePath = stack.slice(idx).concat(toId);\n          cycles.push(cyclePath);\n        }\n      }\n      stack.pop();\n      color.set(nodeId, 2);\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    for(let nid of nodes.keys()){\n      if(color.get(nid) === 0){\n        dfs(nid);\n      }\n    }\n    return cycles;\n  }\n\n  // Calculate max depth of tree from all roots (nodes with no inbound edges)\n  function calcMaxDepth() {\n    if(nodes.size === 0) return 0;\n\n    // Find roots (no inbound edges)\n    let inbound = new Map();\n    for(let nid of nodes.keys()){\n      inbound.set(nid, 0);\n    }\n    for(let node of nodes.values()){\n      for(let b of node.branches){\n        if(inbound.has(b.toNodeId)) inbound.set(b.toNodeId, inbound.get(b.toNodeId)+1);\n      }\n    }\n    let roots = Array.from(inbound.entries()).filter(([nid, count]) => count === 0).map(([nid]) => nid);\n    if(roots.length === 0){\n      roots = Array.from(nodes.keys());\n    }\n\n    let memo = new Map();\n\n    function dfsDepth(nid) {\n      if(memo.has(nid)) return memo.get(nid);\n      let node = nodes.get(nid);\n      if(!node || node.branches.length === 0) {\n        memo.set(nid, 1);\n        return 1;\n      }\n      let maxChildDepth = 0;\n      for(let b of node.branches){\n        let d = dfsDepth(b.toNodeId);\n        if(d > maxChildDepth) maxChildDepth = d;\n      }\n      memo.set(nid, 1 + maxChildDepth);\n      return 1+ maxChildDepth;\n    }\n\n    let maxDepth = 0;\n    roots.forEach(rid => {\n      let d = dfsDepth(rid);\n      if(d > maxDepth) maxDepth = d;\n    });\n    return maxDepth;\n  }\n\n  // Find leaves (nodes with no branches out)\n  function findLeaves() {\n    let leaves = [];\n    for(let [nid, node] of nodes.entries()){\n      if(node.branches.length === 0){\n        leaves.push(nid);\n      }\n    }\n    return leaves;\n  }\n\n  // Event listeners\n\n  btnAddNode.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if(simActive){\n      alert('Stop simulation before adding nodes.');\n      return;\n    }\n    let label = sanitizeLabel(inputNewNodeLabel.value);\n    if(!label) {\n      displayMessage('Please enter a valid node label.', true);\n      return;\n    }\n    addNode(label);\n    inputNewNodeLabel.value = '';\n    refreshAll();\n    displayMessage(`Node added: \"${label}\"`, false);\n  });\n\n  btnClearAll.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if(!confirm('Are you sure you want to clear all nodes and branches? This cannot be undone.')) return;\n    nodes.clear();\n    nextNodeId = 1;\n    resetSimulation();\n    refreshAll();\n    displayMessage('All nodes and branches cleared.', false);\n  });\n\n  branchForm.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if(simActive) {\n      alert('Stop simulation before adding branches.');\n      return;\n    }\n    let fromId = branchFromSelect.value;\n    let toId = branchToSelect.value;\n    let condition = sanitizeLabel(branchConditionInput.value);\n    if(!fromId || !toId || !condition){\n      displayMessage('Please fill all branch fields.', true);\n      return;\n    }\n    if(fromId === toId){\n      if(!confirm('Branch from a node to itself. Are you sure?')) return;\n    }\n    if(!addBranch(fromId, condition, toId)) {\n      displayMessage('Failed to add branch. Condition labels must be unique for the same node.', true);\n      return;\n    }\n    branchConditionInput.value = '';\n    refreshAll();\n    displayMessage(`Branch added: From ID:${fromId} [${condition}] to ID:${toId}`, false);\n  });\n\n  btnClearBranches.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if(simActive){\n      alert('Stop simulation before clearing branches.');\n      return;\n    }\n    if(!confirm('Clear all branches?')) return;\n    clearAllBranches();\n    refreshAll();\n    displayMessage('All branches cleared.', false);\n  });\n\n  btnStartSim.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    let startId = simStartNodeSelect.value;\n    if(!startId || !nodes.has(startId)){\n      alert('Please select a valid start node.');\n      return;\n    }\n    startSimulation(startId);\n    displayMessage(`Simulation started at node ID:${startId}`, false);\n  });\n\n  btnEndSim.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    endSimulation();\n  });\n\n  btnImportJson.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if(simActive){\n      alert('Stop simulation before importing.');\n      return;\n    }\n    let text = jsonTextarea.value.trim();\n    if(!text) {\n      displayJsonMessage('Paste some JSON to import.', true);\n      return;\n    }\n    if(importFromJson(text)){\n      jsonTextarea.value = '';\n    }\n  });\n\n  btnExportJson.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    let json = exportToJson();\n    jsonTextarea.value = json;\n    displayJsonMessage('Export completed. JSON updated in textarea.', false);\n  });\n\n  btnValidateTree.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    let output = [];\n    let cycles = findCycles();\n    let unconnected = findUnconnectedNodes();\n\n    if(cycles.length === 0) {\n      output.push('No cycles detected.');\n    } else {\n      output.push(`Cycles found (${cycles.length}):`);\n      cycles.forEach((cycle, i) => {\n        let pathLabels = cycle.map(nid => {\n          let n = nodes.get(nid);\n          return `ID:${nid} (${n ? n.label : 'broken'})`;\n        });\n        output.push(` ${i+1}. ${pathLabels.join(' → ')}`);\n      });\n    }\n\n    if(unconnected.length === 0){\n      output.push('No unconnected nodes detected.');\n    } else {\n      output.push(`Unconnected nodes (${unconnected.length}):`);\n      unconnected.forEach(nid => {\n        let n = nodes.get(nid);\n        output.push(` - ID:${nid} (${n ? n.label : 'broken'})`);\n      });\n    }\n    displayAnalysis(output.join('\\n'));\n  });\n\n  btnShowDepth.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    let depth = calcMaxDepth();\n    displayAnalysis(`Maximum decision tree depth: ${depth}`);\n  });\n\n  btnShowLeaves.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    let leaves = findLeaves();\n    if(leaves.length === 0) {\n      displayAnalysis('No leaf nodes found (every node has at least one outgoing branch).');\n    } else {\n      let lines = ['Leaf nodes (no outgoing branches):'];\n      for(let nid of leaves) {\n        let n = nodes.get(nid);\n        lines.push(` - ID:${nid} (${n ? n.label : 'broken'})`);\n      }\n      displayAnalysis(lines.join('\\n'));\n    }\n  });\n\n\n  // Initialize UI on page load\n  refreshAll();\n  resetSimulation();\n\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
